  "tune": "Aurelia",
  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "O Father, all crea- ting, Whose wisdom, love, and pow&#39;r First bound two lives together In Eden&#39;s primal hour, Today to these Thy children Thy earliest gifts renew: A home by Thee made happy, A love by Thee kept true.",
    "v2": "O Savior, Guest most bounteous Of old in Galilee, Vouchsafe today Thy presence With these who call on Thee; Their store of earthly gladness Transform to heav&#39;nly wine, And teach them, in the tasting To know the gift is Thine.",
    "v3": "O Spirit of the Father, Breathe on them from above, So mighty in Thy pureness, So tender in Thy love; That, guarded by Thy presence, From sin and strife kept free, Their lives may own Thy guidance, Their hearts be rul&#39;d by Thee.",
    "v4": "Except Thou build it, Father, The house is built in vain; Except Thou, Savior, bless it, The joy will turn to pain; But naught can break the union Of hearts in Thee made one, And love Thy Spirit hallow&#39;d Is endless love begun."
  },
